No, this is when we fight back,
this is when we play dirty,

14:37.849 --> 14:39.377
this is when we make them pay.

14:39.546 --> 14:41.519
We cannot go to war
with a faculty member.

14:41.644 --> 14:43.394
We will all get expelled.

14:43.676 --> 14:46.092
Wait a minute.
We can Borg him.

14:47.019 --> 14:48.202
I'll get Heath.

14:49.199 --> 14:50.263
Absorb him

14:50.432 --> 14:53.932
into our collective.
If he feels like he's one of us,

14:54.057 --> 14:56.436
maybe he will relax the rules.

14:56.792 --> 14:58.583
You know,  that oddly makes sense.

14:58.708 --> 15:01.575
And maybe he could help
you pick a major. He is faculty,

15:02.163 --> 15:05.403
and the one thing old people love
to do more than anything else

15:05.572 --> 15:07.113
is give advice to kids.

15:08.658 --> 15:09.658
Z...

15:10.354 --> 15:11.117
S...

15:11.530 --> 15:13.680
I bet I know who stole the money.

15:14.417 --> 15:16.646
Don't want to be elitist,
but hello ?

15:16.771 --> 15:18.708
- Housekeeping ?
- Everybody, calm down.

15:19.667 --> 15:21.619
Let's not turn this
into a witch-hunt.

15:21.744 --> 15:22.837
I bet it was Trip.

15:22.962 --> 15:25.966
He's the first to blame everyone else
so he can throw suspicion off himself.

15:26.135 --> 15:28.343
What am I supposed to do,
just let us get ripped off ?

15:28.512 --> 15:32.250
No one's saying do nothing, Trip.
There's no reason to turn on each other.

15:32.558 --> 15:35.350
Does it really matter who took it ?
It's only 500 bucks.

15:35.884 --> 15:38.645
Maybe Grant took it. Can't be cheap
to change your look overnight.

15:38.813 --> 15:41.022
Maybe crazy Natalie tricked you
into stealing it for her.

15:41.190 --> 15:43.149
What did I just say
about turning on each other ?

15:43.318 --> 15:46.695
Guys, what I meant is maybe we can all
 pitch in a little cash and cover it.

15:46.864 --> 15:48.721
- Problem solved.
- It's not about the money.

15:48.846 --> 15:51.292
- It's the principle.
- Maybe it was Chambers.

15:51.417 --> 15:54.369
- He needs money the most.
- After everything Evan's been through

15:54.537 --> 15:56.760
with the house,
you think he'd steal the money ?

15:56.885 --> 15:58.235
Maybe it was you.

16:00.348 --> 16:02.085
So much for avoiding a witch-hunt.

16:08.356 --> 16:11.469
So Tom, what does
a music historian actually do ?

16:11.637 --> 16:14.078
I mostly just listen to music.

16:14.475 --> 16:16.182
Boring classically classical stuff ?

16:16.701 --> 16:19.022
Well, I have spent
the last three years

16:19.147 --> 16:21.855
working on Richard Strauss'
Die Agyptische Helena.

16:23.824 --> 16:27.250
- Talk about driving a man to drink.
- Yes ! That's true.

16:27.375 --> 16:28.951
- Do you have any ?
- Take mine.

16:29.076 --> 16:30.530
All right.
Thank you.

16:31.616 --> 16:33.757
You know, in my day,
we used to play a game

16:33.882 --> 16:36.953
that combined eight-ball
and beer pong and gambling.

16:37.122 --> 16:38.705
- Monkey-Hump ?
- Yes !

16:39.178 --> 16:41.166
- I'm undefeated.
- Are you ?

16:41.651 --> 16:42.626
So am I.

16:45.922 --> 16:47.372
Borg-ing commenced.

16:48.530 --> 16:49.674
You know, Tom...

16:50.971 --> 16:52.752
We were just talking about Cappie

16:52.877 --> 16:54.684
having so much trouble
picking a major.

16:54.809 --> 16:57.485
As a professor, you might be able
to give him some advice.

16:57.610 --> 16:59.851
Maybe you can discuss it
while you guys Monkey-Hump.

17:00.019 --> 17:02.187
I'd be more than happy
to help you with that.

17:10.719 --> 17:11.719
It's on.

17:21.853 --> 17:23.540
Can I help you with something ?

17:24.109 --> 17:25.085
No, thanks.

17:29.879 --> 17:32.230
- That was weird.
- I know. She said thanks.

17:32.355 --> 17:36.138
So I will go grab all the nametag stuff.
We have so much catching up to do.

17:36.263 --> 17:38.062
- The... ?
- For the dorm reunion ?

17:38.187 --> 17:40.058
My God !
I totally forgot.

17:40.477 --> 17:42.852
You probably forgot
to pick up the cups, too.

17:43.713 --> 17:44.771
I'm sorry.

17:45.249 --> 17:46.690
Joel blew apart

17:46.859 --> 17:49.734
my personal statement and I've been
trying to come up with a new topic.

17:50.418 --> 17:52.487
That sucks.
You should've told me.

17:52.655 --> 17:55.720
Maybe I can help.
It's all about marketing yourself.

17:55.845 --> 17:59.127
And who knows more about marketing
or yourself, than me and myself ?

17:59.252 --> 18:01.746
I know what your personal statement
should be about. Hi, ZBZ.

18:03.687 --> 18:07.656
Katherine is helping me,
and she already got into law school !

18:08.786 --> 18:11.124
- Awesome !
- The ban on sexual discrimination

18:11.249 --> 18:13.133
was added to the Civil
Rights Act of 1964

18:13.302 --> 18:15.249
by a senator who wanted
to defeat the bill.

18:15.374 --> 18:17.637
- But the bill passed, right ?
- Yes, it did.

18:17.806 --> 18:20.468
But just as justice
triumphed over cynicism,

18:20.593 --> 18:23.185
you do not let the negative
stereotypes of sority girls

18:23.310 --> 18:25.353
dissuade you from achieving

18:25.522 --> 18:27.624
- visionary objectives.
- That is perfect !

18:27.749 --> 18:29.073
Right, Ash ?

18:29.645 --> 18:30.358
Yeah.

18:30.989 --> 18:33.737
So I'll just go do those nametags.

18:33.906 --> 18:36.322
Looks like you guys
got this under control.

18:39.791 --> 18:41.578
Don't forget the cups, Case.

18:42.936 --> 18:43.663
Right.

18:53.208 --> 18:54.258
No problem.

18:55.450 --> 18:56.763
You have a second ?

18:56.888 --> 18:59.545
You wanna see this awesome video
of this robot hand ?

18:59.670 --> 19:01.420
That Katherine sent you ?

19:02.482 --> 19:04.711
She's kind of cool and interesting.

19:04.836 --> 19:06.940
I wish everyone felt that way.

19:07.065 --> 19:10.064
- I think Ashleigh's jealous of her.
- Then I can't help you.

19:10.232 --> 19:13.002
Guys don't get jealous. That way,
we have more time to invent things

19:13.127 --> 19:16.237
- and cure diseases.
- And start wars and light farts ?

19:16.406 --> 19:18.254
Well, thanks, Rus.
Big help.

19:18.773 --> 19:21.326
Where's Cappie ?
How's his major hunt going ?

19:21.495 --> 19:23.760
I think I may have found him
an academic adviser.

19:23.885 --> 19:24.662
Great !

19:24.831 --> 19:27.276
I don't want to sound like
one of those nagging girlfriends

19:27.401 --> 19:30.325
and it's not like I'm worried
he's gonna end up being...

19:30.450 --> 19:33.377
one of those 40-year-olds guys
still partying at the KT house...

19:35.380 --> 19:37.005
I'm starving !

19:38.953 --> 19:39.928
Gotta get up !

19:41.426 --> 19:42.263
Oh, man...

19:45.482 --> 19:48.144
That's not his academic adviser,
right ?

19:48.313 --> 19:50.207
No. That's...

19:51.275 --> 19:52.232
Pickle's dad.

19:57.245 --> 19:59.841
David Sedaris is doing a reading
on campus this weekend.

19:59.966 --> 20:01.658
- You wanna go ?
- Sounds fun.

20:04.593 --> 20:06.621
That was pretty gutsy of you,
taking on Trip.

20:07.331 --> 20:09.290
Why ?
Evan's my big brother.

20:09.459 --> 20:11.532
Haven't you thought
maybe he stole the money ?

20:11.657 --> 20:14.415
- He's broke. He needs the cash.
- And he has a job.

20:14.540 --> 20:17.155
As far as I know, he's not investing
in home hair products

20:17.280 --> 20:18.758
and velvet suits.

20:20.020 --> 20:23.562
- So now you think that I did it ?
- No, I'm just merely pointing out

20:23.687 --> 20:26.287
why we shouldn't be
throwing around blame.

20:26.996 --> 20:27.851
Hi, guys.

20:30.899 --> 20:32.975
- What are you doing ?
- Waiting for Evan.

20:33.100 --> 20:34.607
No, to the couch.

20:35.580 --> 20:38.653
- Redecorating.
- Let us know if you find $500 in there.

20:39.924 --> 20:42.367
Hey, feeling better ?

20:42.492 --> 20:44.993
Yeah, must've been one
of those 24 hour things.

20:45.161 --> 20:47.819
- I'm really hungry now.
- Okay, let's go.

20:49.445 --> 20:51.903
So we shouldn't be throwing
blame around, even though last night

20:52.028 --> 20:54.168
you were pissed that someone
stole from their brothers ?

20:54.337 --> 20:55.911
I don't like any of it, OK ?

20:56.036 --> 20:57.773
The money was stolen on my watch,

20:57.898 --> 21:00.848
so everyone's looking at me
to fix the situation.

21:02.048 --> 21:04.304
Maybe there's a way we can solve
both problems at once.

21:04.472 --> 21:07.640
Get the money back and not
publicly humiliate anyone.

21:12.626 --> 21:14.274
Tom didn't go home last night ?

21:14.399 --> 21:16.720
No, he told Margie he was up all night
grading papers.

21:16.845 --> 21:18.934
You're a genius, Spitter.
I think we Borged him.

21:19.059 --> 21:21.941
He dropped the curfews and told us not
to worry about the house-butt problem.

21:22.066 --> 21:25.670
So mission accomplished, right ?
You can send him home.

21:25.795 --> 21:27.571
No way, I made him
an honorary pledge.

21:27.696 --> 21:29.846
He came as Tom.
Now, he's T-Bag.

21:30.498 --> 21:32.565
So did T-Bag help you
with your major ?

21:32.690 --> 21:36.473
I found out what old people love more
than giving advice : being young people.

21:37.838 --> 21:40.173
I can't believe I Monkey-Humped you
twice last night.

21:40.342 --> 21:42.091
Do you guys ever do keg stands ?

21:42.689 --> 21:45.053
Hi, there.
Have you seen Tom ?

21:46.514 --> 21:48.526
No, we haven't, Mrs. Hilgendorf.

21:48.651 --> 21:51.184
May I say that blouse
brings out the color in your eyes ?

21:51.605 --> 21:54.020
And the lemon bars... to die for.

21:54.444 --> 21:55.855
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

21:56.024 --> 21:59.400
And if we see Tom, we'll be sure
to tell him you came by looking for him.

21:59.569 --> 22:02.070
Of course.
Have a nice day.

22:05.116 --> 22:06.407
Dude, thank you.

22:06.576 --> 22:08.096
She would've had my ass.

22:08.221 --> 22:10.495
And not in a...
Like in a good way.

22:10.664 --> 22:13.706
It's the least I can do for the best
academic adviser at CRU

22:14.523 --> 22:16.167
Do you wanna watch sports all day ?

22:16.336 --> 22:18.378
Okay !
Let me get my beers !

22:21.793 --> 22:24.926
- What's up, guys ?
- When's the old dude leaving ?

22:25.095 --> 22:26.928
Because if I wanted to spend time
with a guy

22:27.096 --> 22:29.639
old enough to be my dad,
I'd go home and hang with my dad.

22:29.808 --> 22:32.244
He's not doing too much
for Cappie at this point either.

22:32.369 --> 22:34.560
You invited him here,
so make him go.

22:34.728 --> 22:37.146
How ? Cappie already made him
an honorary pledge.

22:37.315 --> 22:40.274
You're Pledge Educator.
Just haze him until he quits.

22:43.101 --> 22:45.088
Pledge T-Bag ?
Yes ?

22:45.740 --> 22:46.698
Give me five ?

22:48.454 --> 22:49.784
These are mine.

22:51.546 --> 22:52.453
Pushups ?

22:53.170 --> 22:55.039
Hazing ! Fun !

22:55.208 --> 22:56.416
Okay, let's do them !

23:08.470 --> 23:10.596
- Five more ?
- OK. Wait a minute.

23:10.765 --> 23:13.516
Shouldn't all the other pledges
be doing this with me ?

23:15.102 --> 23:18.229
Sorry, guys.
Ten from everyone.

23:18.398 --> 23:19.978
Come on, you guys !

23:26.030 --> 23:27.030
Yeah.

23:27.765 --> 23:28.614
Good.

23:29.200 --> 23:30.658
I'll prepare the SOUF.

23:31.581 --> 23:33.161
What's that ?
What's the SOUF ?

23:34.496 --> 23:36.330
Smoothie Of Unidentified Fluids.

23:37.666 --> 23:39.916
And you're gonna love your costume.

23:45.141 --> 23:47.278
You should probably
start getting ready.

23:47.403 --> 23:50.178
Can I meet you there ?
I just want to read through this again.

23:51.197 --> 23:53.806
I thought "Gamma Psi"
figured it all out for you.

23:55.600 --> 23:57.535
Katherine has really smart advice.

23:57.660 --> 23:59.540
She's already gotten
into Yale Law and...

23:59.665 --> 24:02.054
she knows what the admissions
committees are looking for.

24:02.179 --> 24:03.815
But does she know you ?

24:03.985 --> 24:06.173
I gotta tell you,
when I think of Casey Cartwright,

24:06.298 --> 24:09.298
I'm not reminded
of the Civil Rights Act of 1964.

24:09.782 --> 24:12.617
Well, it's a good thing you're not
on the admissions committees.

24:12.786 --> 24:16.659
Why is it even called a personal
statement, if it's just a bunch of BS ?

24:16.784 --> 24:19.707
Look, I don't care
if it's BS or personal.

24:19.876 --> 24:23.503
I just want to get into law school
and with Katherine's input, I will.

24:24.677 --> 24:26.377
You're sure about that ?

24:29.505 --> 24:30.895
I'm so sure,

24:31.506 --> 24:33.888
I am going to go with you
to that reunion.

24:34.057 --> 24:36.007
Great.
Don't forget the cups.

24:37.062 --> 24:38.062
Again.

24:40.326 --> 24:41.726
No dust.
Anywhere.

24:42.298 --> 24:45.198
Beaver, did you find
any jewelry in your room ?

24:45.323 --> 24:46.323
Leave.

24:47.828 --> 24:48.945
A silver necklace ?

24:49.614 --> 24:51.572
Why would that be in my room ?

24:52.787 --> 24:54.659
I think I lost it when we...

24:56.937 --> 24:57.987
You know...

24:59.522 --> 25:03.084
God, you're gonna make me say it.
When we had sex.

25:03.436 --> 25:06.212
We did do it !
I bet Wonder Woman really happened, too.

25:07.756 --> 25:09.674
Don't worry.
You were way better.

25:13.491 --> 25:14.891
What, I'm serious.

25:15.979 --> 25:18.057
You're charming
when you're not trying so hard.

25:18.299 --> 25:20.434
Wanna go upstairs
and lose your earrings ?

25:20.603 --> 25:23.903
And now you're back.
Come on, help me find my necklace.

25:29.426 --> 25:30.903
How's it going, Pledge T-Bag ?

25:31.071 --> 25:34.129
- What do I clean next ?
- You wanna play some beer pong ?

25:34.254 --> 25:36.868
He was just about to clean
underneath the pool table.

25:37.296 --> 25:38.744
Oh, you guys !

25:41.296 --> 25:43.791
So I think Tom has helped me
decide what to major in.

25:43.960 --> 25:45.168
- Really ?
- Yes.

25:45.337 --> 25:46.993
I wanna major in Tom.

25:49.089 --> 25:52.128
I want to be having that much fun
when I'm elderly. He's awesome.

25:52.253 --> 25:53.509
No, he isn't.

25:53.677 --> 25:56.762
He's creeping everybody out. Not to
mention, no girl will ever set foot

25:56.931 --> 25:59.901
in Kappa Tau once they know we're
recruiting senior citizens as pledges.

26:00.026 --> 26:02.667
Untrue. Girls love it here.
Look.

26:03.684 --> 26:06.397
What ? That's Dumptruck.
And who's he with ?

26:10.225 --> 26:11.225
Dad ?

26:11.741 --> 26:13.946
You're drinking ?
What is this ?

26:14.288 --> 26:16.031
I can't find my necklace.

26:17.209 --> 26:19.259
- Noise disturbance !
- Huck ?

26:19.454 --> 26:20.703
Oh no, campus cops.

26:22.498 --> 26:24.540
- Officer Huck.
- Hucky !

26:24.708 --> 26:26.209
The old Huckster !

26:42.351 --> 26:46.355
I couldn't do it all by myself. Kinda
like you and your personal statement.

26:47.092 --> 26:49.321
Well, this'll be a fun
walk down memory lane.

26:49.446 --> 26:52.046
I'm gonna go put these
by the punch bowl.

26:53.576 --> 26:54.576
My God !

26:56.037 --> 26:58.574
And Ashleigh ?
Is that you ?

26:59.046 --> 27:00.405
It is.
Hi, Sunny.

27:00.530 --> 27:02.823
Well, I haven't seen you guys
in, like, forever !

27:02.948 --> 27:05.713
- What have you been up to these days ?
- Ashleigh was just talking

27:05.838 --> 27:08.626
about how she made
these nametags all by herself.

27:08.794 --> 27:11.128
So cute.
And what about you ?

27:11.490 --> 27:13.464
Well, she's applying to law school.

27:13.633 --> 27:16.634
It's a visionary objective and nothing
will stop her from achieving it.

27:19.553 --> 27:21.504
You two really stuck together.
You know...

27:21.629 --> 27:24.724
I've lost touch with almost everyone
from the dorm.

27:24.893 --> 27:27.365
- We've been roommates.
- That explains it.

27:27.490 --> 27:30.434
You can't help be friends with
the people you live with. Kind of like

27:30.559 --> 27:32.814
how we were all friends because
the university randomly

27:32.939 --> 27:36.195
assigned us to Pierson. It's not like
we had a ton in common or anything !

27:37.865 --> 27:40.449
I guess that's why reunions
are so awkward.

27:40.618 --> 27:43.588
If you wanted awkward, you should've
been at the ZBZ house last night.

27:43.713 --> 27:45.705
Casey was under some serious
mind control.

27:46.476 --> 27:48.768
- Were you playing Ouija ?
- All she was doing

27:48.893 --> 27:51.669
was helping with my statement,
which is the key to my whole future.

27:51.838 --> 27:54.463
Which evidently is more important
than your past.

27:54.632 --> 27:56.739
What is your problem ?
Why are you so jealous ?

27:56.864 --> 27:59.385
This isn't about Katherine.
And my problem is

27:59.554 --> 28:03.557
that we're not on the same page at all
anymore and you don't even realize it.

28:07.686 --> 28:10.163
It was great to see you both again.

28:17.321 --> 28:19.424
If Huck finds out
we have a 16-year-old girl

28:19.549 --> 28:22.873
hanging out at the house with alcohol,
we'll be kicked off the Row.

28:22.998 --> 28:25.411
And my dad'll get fired
for partying with students.

28:25.579 --> 28:27.066
Relax, it's just Huck.

28:27.191 --> 28:30.100
We've Dewey and Anthony Hopkins
keeping him occupied inside.

28:30.225 --> 28:32.348
We'll just walk our
Hilgendorfs out the back gate

28:32.473 --> 28:35.223
and in through their front door,
all right ?

28:37.959 --> 28:38.959
Open it !

28:41.101 --> 28:42.728
Over the fence.

28:43.587 --> 28:45.487
Who's going over the fence ?

28:47.684 --> 28:48.984
One, two, three.

28:50.377 --> 28:52.313
- Up, up !
- This was a bad idea !

28:52.481 --> 28:54.732
A lot of broken glass there.

28:55.166 --> 28:57.902
- It seems quiet to me.
- That's because you're a civilian.

28:58.296 --> 29:00.346
Every night, I train my ears...

29:00.866 --> 29:02.405
to detect a pin drop.

29:03.659 --> 29:05.009
By dropping pins.

29:07.287 --> 29:08.937
And that was not a pin.

29:15.467 --> 29:17.017
What are they doing ?

29:19.744 --> 29:20.744
Tai chi.

29:29.064 --> 29:30.114
And exhale.

29:30.728 --> 29:31.519
Namaste.

29:31.965 --> 29:33.015
Breathe in.

29:34.694 --> 29:36.482
What ?
I took a Learning Annex class.

29:41.714 --> 29:44.406
Hey, guys !
You forgot to unhook the latch.

29:47.286 --> 29:50.736
I just landed in the garden.
Our tomatoes are doing great.

29:51.834 --> 29:52.873
Mom's home !

29:54.792 --> 29:57.492
Maybe she won't be
that angry with T-Bag...

29:57.701 --> 29:59.296
T-Dad... your dad.

29:59.795 --> 30:00.897
Are you kidding ?

30:01.022 --> 30:03.797
If she finds out, she'll divorce Dad,
send me off to boarding school

30:03.922 --> 30:05.886
- and shut your house down.
- Okay, plan B.

30:06.054 --> 30:09.454
Rebecca, you and Beav stall Mom.
We'll get them upstairs.

30:10.634 --> 30:12.079
I'll open a window.

30:13.770 --> 30:15.383
This is not a part of Plan B.

30:15.508 --> 30:17.558
I didn't hear anything about...

30:20.032 --> 30:20.901
What's up ?

30:21.070 --> 30:23.433
We are giving whoever did this
a chance to return the money

30:23.558 --> 30:25.971
- without all the finger-pointing.
- Everyone gets an envelope,

30:26.096 --> 30:28.993
which we all have to place
in a sealed box in the Chapter Room.

30:29.162 --> 30:31.495
Whoever stole the money can return it
without anyone knowing.

30:31.620 --> 30:34.530
And as long as it's returned,
there's no need to punish anyone.

30:34.655 --> 30:36.055
Makes sense to me.

30:46.975 --> 30:48.262
Mrs. Hilgendorf, hi !

30:48.431 --> 30:50.670
I'm Rebecca Logan,
ZBZ's Welcome Wagon.

30:50.795 --> 30:53.845
- I'm Beaver, and I'm with her.
- Trying too hard.

30:55.395 --> 30:56.793
Watch your head.

30:56.918 --> 30:59.190
So, what were Rebecca and
Beaver doing upstairs ?

30:59.359 --> 31:01.400
Taking cultures for her bio class.

31:01.569 --> 31:04.951
If I didn't know any better,
I'd think they slept together.

31:05.076 --> 31:07.323
- They did ?
- Leave it alone, Spitter.

31:08.300 --> 31:10.659
- This looks like my house !
- That's because it is.

31:10.827 --> 31:11.869
That's my bed.

31:13.163 --> 31:16.147
- We're gonna put you in bed.
- Good idea. I'm tired.

31:16.272 --> 31:19.293
- Let's get you in there.
- Guys, I'm really tired.

31:23.112 --> 31:24.882
We should, like, grab a movie.

31:25.355 --> 31:27.468
- Stay away from my daughter !
- Dad !

31:32.364 --> 31:34.642
- He's all tucked in.
- Spray him and get out of here.

31:39.073 --> 31:41.789
We could use Rebecca and Beaver
to get back at Evan

31:41.914 --> 31:44.118
- for getting the guys expelled.
- We're gonna get back

31:44.243 --> 31:46.105
at all the Omega Chis for that
and when we do,

31:46.230 --> 31:48.531
we won't need to drag
anybody else into it.

31:49.428 --> 31:51.528
We gotta lose the costume, guys.

31:52.561 --> 31:53.711
Get his hat !

31:55.527 --> 31:57.915
Sorry, did you say
your name was Beaver ?

31:58.693 --> 32:00.251
It's short for "The Beaver."

32:01.351 --> 32:02.795
If you'll excuse me...

32:04.730 --> 32:06.340
Look up here !
Look up here !

32:07.140 --> 32:09.184
That was the signal.
We gotta hurry up.

32:09.681 --> 32:10.881
Just a call...

32:12.853 --> 32:14.253
It's a... welcome.

32:14.546 --> 32:15.596
Good night.

32:19.328 --> 32:21.128
That's Rebecca's necklace.

32:30.407 --> 32:31.807
- Are you OK ?
- No !

32:33.788 --> 32:35.138
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

32:41.275 --> 32:42.543
Time to go to bed.

32:48.466 --> 32:50.561
And there are two of
us in this friendship.

32:50.686 --> 32:52.816
So it can't be all my fault, right ?

32:52.941 --> 32:56.010
- It's possible, but not very probable.
- I know !

32:56.962 --> 32:58.475
I mean, yes, I have

32:58.643 --> 33:01.122
been a little focused on law school,

33:01.247 --> 33:03.400
but she's been dealing
with other stuff, too.

33:03.525 --> 33:06.525
Who's to say which one of us turned
the page when the other wasn't looking ?

33:06.693 --> 33:08.703
I've never been on
the same page with anyone.

33:08.828 --> 33:12.082
I joined GP only for the networking
connections after college. But Casey,

33:12.207 --> 33:15.159
- I do consider you to be...
- On the same page ?

33:15.594 --> 33:17.161
I was gonna say a friend.

33:18.997 --> 33:20.442
So we're friends ?

33:21.702 --> 33:25.461
Yes and I was thinking that maybe one
day we could be the kind of friends

33:25.629 --> 33:27.546
- could read each other's...
- Minds ?

33:27.980 --> 33:29.214
I was gonna say books.

33:29.826 --> 33:30.617
Right.

33:30.742 --> 33:33.552
But I think it takes a little
bit to get on the same page.

33:33.720 --> 33:35.888
Have you read the recent
works of Alice Munro ?

33:40.477 --> 33:42.978
- The recent works ?
- No.

33:43.146 --> 33:44.440
This is a first edition.

33:44.565 --> 33:48.150
I just wrote my name on the inside
cover so you know who to return it to.

33:50.314 --> 33:51.111
Thanks.

33:54.931 --> 33:57.227
And I'm sorry that you
and Ashleigh have grown apart.

33:57.352 --> 33:59.702
But it happens to a lot of people
at the end of college.

34:00.707 --> 34:03.468
Maybe some people should
be around your entire life,

34:03.593 --> 34:06.001
and others should just
make an appearance.

34:26.022 --> 34:27.511
Dryer sheets and...

34:28.126 --> 34:29.126
and...

34:29.956 --> 34:30.775
Mold.

34:32.638 --> 34:33.638
Yeah.

34:35.905 --> 34:37.783
Well, Sunny seemed sunny.

34:37.951 --> 34:39.625
No one should smile that much.

34:39.918 --> 34:42.329
She's gonna need Botox
by the time she's 25.

34:42.496 --> 34:43.789
Or a lobotomy.

34:47.540 --> 34:49.293
I can't believe this
is where we met.

34:49.664 --> 34:52.975
- And where we met Frannie.
- You had to say the "F" word.

34:54.425 --> 34:58.204
How different would college
have been without this ten-foot,

34:58.329 --> 35:00.338
poorly-ventilated and moldy room ?

35:01.016 --> 35:03.057
Things were a lot easier back then.

35:04.064 --> 35:04.935
For us.

35:05.312 --> 35:06.625
Yeah, we were freshmen.

35:06.750 --> 35:10.679
Our biggest concern was whether
or not the dryer was eating our socks.

35:12.449 --> 35:13.449
And now ?

35:14.078 --> 35:14.945
Now...

35:15.951 --> 35:17.920
we both have a lot more going on.

35:18.634 --> 35:20.181
Boyfriends in different houses,

35:20.306 --> 35:22.185
schedules that demand our attention,

35:22.310 --> 35:24.955
plans after graduation
that are changing our priorities.

35:26.278 --> 35:28.228
We'll have to work harder to...

35:28.353 --> 35:29.918
stay on the same page.

35:30.614 --> 35:32.794
We never had to work at it before.

35:34.118 --> 35:35.118
I know.

35:36.098 --> 35:37.098
I know.

35:40.791 --> 35:42.432
Do you think that Sunny was right ?

35:42.557 --> 35:45.157
We're only friends
because of geography ?

35:46.887 --> 35:49.289
Maybe that's why we became friends,

35:49.414 --> 35:51.482
but I don't think it's
why we stayed friends.

35:53.154 --> 35:55.068
You don't think
that we're growing apart ?

35:57.527 --> 35:58.947
I think we're growing up.

36:00.434 --> 36:02.941
Ash, I don't want to live in the past.
Not with you.

36:03.539 --> 36:06.398
- Because if we did, we'd still be...
- In this laundry room ?

36:11.851 --> 36:14.296
Well, I can still read your mind.

36:18.234 --> 36:19.234
So who...

36:20.191 --> 36:21.720
is Alice Munro ?

36:22.453 --> 36:23.484
You know...

36:24.386 --> 36:25.224
no clue.

36:32.268 --> 36:34.918
But we got away with it,
that's something.

36:36.616 --> 36:37.528
Not really.

36:38.327 --> 36:40.155
Guys, I'm a 40-year-old man

36:40.280 --> 36:42.741
and I just had to rely on
a bunch of guys in their twenties

36:42.909 --> 36:44.910
to rescue me
and my 16-year-old daughter.

36:45.078 --> 36:46.078
I'm 19.

36:47.244 --> 36:48.405
Way to rub it in.

36:48.979 --> 36:50.791
- Sorry about hazing you.
- No.

36:51.451 --> 36:53.338
No reason to be.
You guys are great.

36:53.463 --> 36:55.471
I just don't think
I'm supposed to be here.

36:55.596 --> 36:57.548
- But you're T-Bag.
- No.

36:58.424 --> 36:59.584
I'm just Dad,

36:59.947 --> 37:01.857
and sometimes Professor Hilgendorf.

37:02.796 --> 37:04.776
No offense, but that's depressing.

37:05.198 --> 37:07.933
Yeah, to you, it is.
But I like my life, really.

37:08.101 --> 37:10.023
And while it was fun to play around,

37:10.148 --> 37:12.312
I belong on the other
side of the fence.

37:15.216 --> 37:17.233
- What about the rules ?
- Forget about that.

37:17.358 --> 37:19.319
College is not supposed
to be about rules.

37:19.487 --> 37:21.637
You guys have your fun.
As a matter of fact,

37:21.762 --> 37:24.658
have a lot of fun and I will live
vicariously through you.

37:25.030 --> 37:28.124
Well, Tom, the table's always open
if you want to get Monkey-Humped.

37:28.714 --> 37:31.069
No, I think I'm gonna
retire undefeated.

37:31.784 --> 37:33.000
Too bad you won't.

37:37.350 --> 37:38.733
Come on, tell me the truth.

37:39.632 --> 37:41.498
You're gonna miss all this,
aren't you ?

37:42.635 --> 37:43.854
Yeah, I'll miss it.

37:45.330 --> 37:47.180
But it's never
the same after you leave.

37:48.037 --> 37:49.766
The truth is you can't go back.

37:50.264 --> 37:52.045
So enjoy it while you can.

37:57.144 --> 38:00.152
Sorry Tom didn't turn out
to be much of an adviser.

38:02.049 --> 38:03.155
You know, Spitter,

38:04.744 --> 38:06.325
he actually made a lot of sense.

38:23.011 --> 38:24.861
And our books are balanced.

38:25.683 --> 38:26.683
Great.

38:27.722 --> 38:28.765
OK. Well,

38:29.667 --> 38:30.886
that ends that.

38:32.242 --> 38:33.242
No...

38:33.847 --> 38:34.770
not quite.

38:35.347 --> 38:37.814
You see, Grant didn't trust you,
but I did.

38:38.090 --> 38:40.410
I told him he was wrong to
think you stole that money.

38:40.738 --> 38:42.319
I told Trip that, too.

38:43.586 --> 38:44.696
What you getting at ?

38:45.918 --> 38:47.054
I trusted you.

38:50.273 --> 38:51.745
I marked the envelope to prove

38:51.913 --> 38:53.622
that you didn't steal the money.

38:59.963 --> 39:01.617
I need to buy Rebecca present.

39:01.742 --> 39:03.966
- I was gonna pay the house back.
- Forget it.

39:04.134 --> 39:05.438
I don't even care.

39:08.775 --> 39:10.430
This isn't an excuse,

39:11.447 --> 39:15.435
but I've been surrounded by money
my entire life, including here.

39:17.897 --> 39:20.030
I guess I'm still
getting used to it.

39:21.202 --> 39:22.713
It's like you said,

39:23.534 --> 39:25.112
living in the straight world.

39:26.299 --> 39:28.209
Please tell me you
didn't just compare me

39:28.334 --> 39:31.159
listening to Lady Gaga to you
being a thief and a liar.

39:31.327 --> 39:33.954
No, that...
That's not what I meant.

39:36.425 --> 39:37.807
Cal, I'm sorry.

39:39.729 --> 39:41.294
I just hoped you could understand.

39:41.462 --> 39:43.491
I just don't think you understand.

39:44.311 --> 39:46.216
You gave up that trust fund up

39:46.384 --> 39:49.130
because you didn't like what
that money was turning you into.

39:49.255 --> 39:51.646
I'm just starting to think
the money wasn't the problem.

39:55.954 --> 39:57.524
Well, you're not expelled.

39:57.758 --> 39:59.891
We live to party another day.

40:00.899 --> 40:02.446
Thank you, by the way.

40:02.821 --> 40:03.821
And...

40:06.965 --> 40:08.148
you're welcome.

40:10.762 --> 40:12.191
Why is there hair in it ?

40:12.508 --> 40:15.168
That's the hair of
a champion Monkey-Humper.

40:18.562 --> 40:20.571
Don't you think you're giving Evan
the wrong idea

40:20.696 --> 40:23.295
by keeping that when you
don't feel the same way he does ?

40:23.463 --> 40:26.004
Evan knew how I felt about
that stuff from the start.

40:28.477 --> 40:30.750
And I don't want to get
so serious with him.

40:32.004 --> 40:33.805
Or with anyone, for that matter.

40:35.051 --> 40:37.875
It's easier and I'm just
not that kind of person.

40:38.645 --> 40:41.519
Why is it so hard to just keep
everything casual and fun ?

40:43.512 --> 40:45.400
Nobody moves, nobody gets hurt.

40:45.568 --> 40:46.973
I'm the one angsting here.

40:47.098 --> 40:49.361
I'm just not sure I'm ready
to graduate and leave here

40:49.582 --> 40:51.578
and become the Hilgendorfs.

40:52.703 --> 40:54.144
The whole idea is...

40:54.779 --> 40:57.321
soul-sucking and kind of scary.

40:58.728 --> 40:59.706
I hear ya.

41:00.368 --> 41:02.079
So, what about you and Casey ?

41:03.064 --> 41:05.293
I thought you didn't want
to be anywhere she isn't.

41:05.418 --> 41:07.973
Well, if she gets into CRU law,
then it won't be an issue

41:08.220 --> 41:09.415
for a while.

41:10.599 --> 41:11.970
And if she doesn't ?

41:13.786 --> 41:15.029
I don't really know.

41:15.154 --> 41:17.099
But I can't figure it
all out today, Becks.

41:17.267 --> 41:20.056
So I'm just gonna hang here
and enjoy the sunshine.

41:21.322 --> 41:22.979
Sounds like a plan to me.

41:23.147 --> 41:24.147
Oh, yeah.

41:25.962 --> 41:27.908
Sounds like quite a laundry room.

41:29.970 --> 41:32.364
The Backstreet Boys
were already taken.

41:32.911 --> 41:35.068
And you never found the sock ?

41:36.122 --> 41:39.954
No, but I realized that legal precedent
isn't all that different from nostalgia.

41:40.079 --> 41:42.165
The law builds on the past

41:42.333 --> 41:44.515
and I wouldn't be who I am,

41:44.640 --> 41:46.320
if it weren't for that laundry room.

41:46.542 --> 41:49.191
And if I had dated
a girl who preferred

41:49.316 --> 41:52.730
U2 to the Backstreet Boys,
I might not be divorced.

41:53.004 --> 41:54.446
It's an interesting theory.

41:54.571 --> 41:56.801
Interesting,
as in "this girl belongs in law school"

41:56.926 --> 41:58.765
or "this girl belongs
in a Laundromat" ?

41:59.450 --> 42:01.268
I think you know the answer to that.

42:03.274 --> 42:04.104
Thank you.

42:09.438 --> 42:10.438
Thanks.

